properties.Title: Alberta Emergency Alert - Traffic Hazard Alert
properties.Summary:
Description: There is a traffic collision on Highway 9 at Range Road 73 between Chinook and Cereal. Everyone in the Hamlet of Chinook must evacuate immediately to Youngstown using Highway 9. ### An Evacuation Centre has been opened at the Youngstown Community Hall and everyone displaced by the emergency are to report to the Evacuation Centre. Go to www.511.alberta.ca for road report information.

properties.Summary:

Strong wind gusts, large hail and heavy rain are all threats. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Intense lightning is likely with any thunderstorm that develops. properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain, at times heavy, continues. Rain will continue today as a trough of low pressure remains over the North Coast. Over Haida Gwaii and North Coast inland near Stewart, total rainfall amounts up to 60 mm can be expected by this evening before the rain eases. Additionally, southeast winds of 70 to 90 km/h will develop this afternoon. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
